BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 4 (KCNA) -- The great leader 
President Kim Il-song received messages of greetings from party 
leaders of different countries on his birthday. 
  Messages came from Klaus Riis, chairman of the Central 
Committee of the Communist Party of Denmark (Marxist-Leninist); 
Preben Moller Hansen, chairman of the Danish Workers' Party, 
Common Cause; Betty Frydensbjerg Carlsson, chairman of the 
Communist Party of Denmark; Timo Lahdenmaki, chairman, and 
Heikki Mannikko, general secretary, of the For Peace and 
Socialism - the Communist Workers' Party of Finland; Sylvestre 
Ntibantunganya, president of the National Assembly of the 
Republic of Burundi and chairman of the Front for Democracy of 
Burundi; Ali Hassan, general secretary of the Supreme Council of 
the Nationalist Socialist Party of Syria in Lebanon; Narayan Man 
Bijukchhe, chairman of the Nepal Workers and Peasants Party; Man 
Mohan Adhikari, president of the Central Committee of the Nepal 
Communist Party (United Marxism-Leninism); Samboram Shrestha, 
secretary general of the Central Committee of the Nepal 
Communist League; Guzman Rivera Castaneda, general secretary of 
the Revolutionary Socialist Party of Peru; and Jean Pierre 
Ngambi, general secretary of the Communist Party of Cameroon. 
  Messages of greetings also came from the standing committee 
of the Central Executive Committee of the Communist Party of the 
Russian Federation and the Central Committee of the Sri Lanka 
Communist Party. 
  The messages extend warmest congratulations to President Kim 
Il- song and wish him good health and a long life. 
  They express firm support to and solidarity with the 
Workers' 
Party and people of Korea in their struggle for defending 
sovereignty of the country and achieving the peaceful 
reunification of country and firm belief that friendly and 
cooperative relations between their parties and the Workers' 
Party of Korea and between their people and the Korean people 
will further strengthen and develop. 

